{"article_id":"wQUVVMr5gnWXsGEt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"CHICAGO-Lori Lightfoot , a former federal prosecutor","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"vowing to take down Chicago ' s political machine ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"won the race","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to become the first black woman mayor of Chicago .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"With 94 % of precincts reporting ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Ms. Lightfoot led Cook County Board President Toni Preckwinkle , 74 % to 26 % , on Tuesday night ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"according to data from the Chicago Board of Election Commissioners .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Ms. Lightfoot will also be the first gay person","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"to lead the nation ' s third-largest city .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"\" We were up against powerful interests , a powerful machine , a powerful mayor , \"","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Ms. Lightfoot ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"who will take office in May ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"said in her victory speech .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"\" We can","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"and we will break this city ' s endless cycle of corruption . \"","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Ms. Preckwinkle said","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"she called Ms. Lightfoot","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"to congratulate her","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"just before 9 p.m. local time","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"though she was disappointed ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"she acknowledged the historic nature of the race .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"\" Not long ago , two African-American women","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"vying for this position","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"would have been unthinkable , \"","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"she said .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"\" Tonight is about the path forward . \"","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"The women , both Democrats , were the two top vote-getters in the early round of voting on Feb. 26","depth":4},{"id":28,"text":"that whittled the field of 14 candidates .","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"' Hit the Ground Running '","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"As Chicago elects its first black woman mayor ,","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"other African-American women","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"who have blazed the same trail across the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"talk about their challenges and triumphs ,","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"and share words of wisdom .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Women In","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"Read more from the Journal on women at work and in the world .","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"Ms. Lighfoot will take over a city","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"grappling with problems","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"including violence and trust in police , a falling population and massive pension liabilities .","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"Both candidates said","depth":4},{"id":41,"text":"addressing Chicago ' s pervasive violence is a priority","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"and would affect how they deal with the city ' s struggling schools , communities and finances .","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"During the campaign , Ms. Lightfoot sought to link Ms. Preckwinkle with the city ' s corrupt political machine ,","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"while Ms. Preckwinkle questioned Ms. Lightfoot ' s previous leadership of a police-accountability task force .","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"Despite the vitriol of the campaign ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"Ms. Lighfoot struck a note of unity with Ms. Preckwinkle on Tuesday night .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"\" Our differences are nothing","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"compared to what we can achieve together , \"","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"she told supporters .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"\" Now that it ' s over","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"I know","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that we will work together for the city","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that we both love . \"","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Ms. Lightfoot ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"who supports more-progressive tax policies ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"one thing","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"the city can do","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"to improve its finances","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"is rein in the millions","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"it spends each year on settlements , judgments and attorney fees .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"She said","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"the city must also do a better job about communicating its financial woes and needs to residents .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"\" We really have to demonstrate to the taxpayers","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"that we ' re not going to continue to treat them like an ATM machine with no limit , \"","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"she said .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Jaime Dominguez , a professor of political science at Northwestern University , said","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"he was stunned by how few Chicago voters turned out on Tuesday .","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"Officials with the Chicago Board of Election Commissioners said","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"32 % of registered voters had cast a ballot in the runoff ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"with turnout largely mirroring that in February .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Officials said","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"mail-in and provisional ballots","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"yet to be counted","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"likely would bump that number up slightly in the coming days .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Mr. Dominguez said","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"Ms. Preckwinkle seemed to struggle in her efforts","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"to persuade voters","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"that she could bring reforms","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"related to criminal justice , housing opportunities and aldermanic privilege .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"\" This wave or undercurrent of antiestablishment politics was definitely prevalent , \"","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"Mr. Dominguez said .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"\" Preckwinkle was just not able to detach herself from the establishment , from the ongoing corruption . \"","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Ms. Lightfoot led in the polls by a substantial margin ahead of election day ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"putting Ms. Preckwinkle and her supporters on the attack .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Some called the acrimony between the two candidates off-putting ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"particularly considering","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that Ms. Preckwinkle would still lead the Cook County Board","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"and the two will have to work together .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"The race was notable for its lack of an overwhelming favorite in a city","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"that has long been dominated by the Daley dynasty and more recently by Mayor Rahm Emanuel , a prominent national Democrat","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"who served in top roles under two presidents","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"before being elected Chicago ' s mayor in 2011 .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Michael Jackson , a 61-year-old teacher from the South Shore on the city ' s majority-black South Side , said","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"he voted for Ms. Lightfoot","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"because she symbolizes change","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"and is a \" fresh voice \" for the city .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"Mr. Jackson said","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"he didn ' t like Ms. Preckwinkle ' s use of attack advertisements","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and thought","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"she relied too heavily on her prior experience .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"\" It ' d be nice","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"if candidates could run on their record","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"rather than tear each other down , \"","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"said Mr. Jackson .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"\" Lightfoot took the high road . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":143,"right":21